      public static <T> java.util.stream.Collector<T,​?,​Array<T>> toList()
      Returns a Collector that accumulates the input elements into a new List. There are no guarantees on the type, mutability, serializability, or thread-safety of the List returned; if more control over the returned List is required, use Collectors.toCollection(Supplier).
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the input elements
      Returns:
      a Collector which collects all the input elements into a List, in encounter order
